channel.description:
We added support for fonts in webpack (woff, woff2, ttf and eot).
The way to use them is as follows:

```
import { css, Global } from "frontity";

// Import your own font file.
import aclonica from "./fonts/aclonica-v10-latin-regular.woff";

const styleWithFont = css`
  @font-face {
    font-family: "Aclonica";
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 400;

    /* Use it inside the CSS */
    src: url(${aclonica});
  }
`;

const Theme = () => (
  ...
  <Global styles={styleWithFont} />
  ...
);
```

Also, several fixes are included in this new release, most related to the `emotion` library:

- The name of the styled component now appears in the CSS class of those components. This makes much easier to identify styled components in the HTML code.

- [Source maps](https://emotion.sh/docs/source-maps) for styled components are fixed too so now they can be properly inspected and debugged using browser dev tools.

> 💡 *To keep Frontity and its packages updated, you can follow [this guide](https://docs.frontity.org/guides/keep-frontity-updated) of our documentation.*

---

### Features

* **webpack:** add support for fonts to webpack ([2148823](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/2148823))

### Bug Fixes

* **core:** add labels and source maps ([#227](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/issues/227)) ([d5af653](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/d5af653))
* **emotion:** fix Global css not ending up in head ([e8c3430](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/e8c3430))
* **emotion:** fix Global leak ([baad509](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/baad509))
* **post-type:** fix handler if a query is present ([0c36a7c](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/0c36a7c))
* **styles:** add styles for form inputs ([#231](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/issues/231)) ([0d6385b](https://github.com/frontity/frontity/commit/0d6385b))

